question.title: The system seems to enter in deadlock when exported to jar

node.contents: There are two things you can try to move on in debugging. First, you can get a thread dump with jps and jstack (these are programs in your $JAVA_HOME/bin directory). Jps will tell you the process IDs of any running processes and jstack will use that process ID to give you a stack trace for every thread (called a thread dump). This will tell you exactly what your code is doing when you think it is deadlocked. Second, you can use your IDE's debugger if you launch your jar with [remote debugging](http://www.ibm.com/developerworks/opensource/library/os-eclipse-javadebug/).

node.contents: The hang has nothing to do with the code you have posted. Based on the thread dump there is no thread in the validaUser method. The reason you see `LS a` is because FileWriter by default works in a non-appending mode. So if validaUser gets called it will write `LS a`. Then it will blow that file away and write `GI a`. Then it will blow that file away and write `LS a` again. If you change your FileWriter constructors to be `new FileWriter("bruno.txt", true)` you will get different results.
